<$fill $name="body">

!! Data flow

# ''Startup'': `startup.js` loads all snapshots from localStorage (compressed), decompresses them, and writes them to `$:/temp/minver/snapshots/<title>` tiddlers
# ''Auto-snapshot on save'': `save-hook.js` hooks `th-saving-tiddler`, captures the current (pre-save) fields, and stores an auto-snapshot
# ''Manual snapshot'': User clicks "Snapshot draft" in the editor → `<$action-minver op="snapshot">` captures draft fields via `storage.js`
# ''Viewing diffs'': The preview pane (`preview-snapshots.tid`) computes a union of snapshot fields and current tiddler fields, then renders per-field `<$diff-text>` comparisons
# ''Rollback'': `<$action-minver op="rollback">` rebuilds the draft tiddler from scratch using only the snapshot's fields (extra fields are removed)

!! Components

|!Component |!Layer |!Role |
|`storage.js` |Browser (library) |Compression, localStorage R/W, eviction, UUID generation, field capture |
|`startup.js` |Browser (startup) |Hydrate `$:/temp/minver/*` from localStorage on wiki load |
|`save-hook.js` |Browser (startup) |`th-saving-tiddler` hook for auto-snapshots, compare state reset |
|`action-minver.js` |Browser (widget) |`<$action-minver>` — snapshot, delete, rollback, export, import, clean |
|`preview-snapshots.tid` |Browser (UI) |Editor preview pane — diff view, toolbar, rollback buttons |
|`manager.tid` |Browser (UI) |Standalone manager — browse, diff, export, import, clean all snapshots |

!! Two-tier storage model

|!Tier |!Persistence |!Auto-snapshots |!Manual snapshots |
|Wiki store (`$:/temp/minver/`) |Session only |Always |Always |
|localStorage |Across reloads |Opt-in via settings |Always |

Both tiers use the same snapshot format. The wiki store is the primary data source for UI rendering. localStorage is the durable backing store loaded on startup.

!! Eviction

Separate counters per tiddler, per type:

* `max-manual` (default: 3) — oldest manual snapshot evicted when exceeded
* `max-auto` (default: 3) — oldest auto snapshot evicted when exceeded
* Manual and auto snapshots never evict each other

!! Design decisions

* ''Browser-only'': No server-side code — works with single-file wikis and Node.js wikis alike
* ''Compressed localStorage'': Native `CompressionStream`/`DecompressionStream` (deflate) + base64 encoding keeps storage footprint small
* ''Temp tiddlers for UI'': Snapshots live in `$:/temp/minver/` so TW's reactive refresh drives the diff UI automatically
* ''Rebuild on rollback'': Rollback constructs a new tiddler from scratch (not merge), ensuring fields added after the snapshot are properly removed
* ''Compare state reset'': The `th-saving-tiddler` hook clears the compare mode state, so the next edit session defaults back to "Draft"

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="warning">
<$fill $name="body">
localStorage is shared across all origins and typically limited to ~5-10MB. Enable "persist auto-snapshots" with caution and monitor usage via the settings page.
</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
</$transclude>
