<$fill $name="body">

!! Restart rules

minver is entirely browser-side. The restart behavior is:

|!File |!Type |!Restart needed? |
|`storage.js` |`module-type: library` |Yes (server restart) |
|`startup.js` |`module-type: startup` |Yes (server restart) |
|`save-hook.js` |`module-type: startup` |Yes (server restart) |
|`action-minver.js` |`module-type: widget` |Yes (server restart) |
|`preview-snapshots.tid` |System tiddler (UI) |Browser reload |
|`manager.tid` |System tiddler (UI) |Browser reload |
|`settings.tid` |System tiddler (UI) |Browser reload |
|`styles.tid` |Stylesheet |Browser reload |
|Config tiddlers |Data |No restart needed |

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">
JS modules require a full server restart. UI tiddlers (`.tid`) are system tiddlers that need a browser reload since `$:/config/SyncSystemTiddlersFromServer` defaults to `"no"`.
</$fill>
</$transclude>

!! File layout

```
minver/
├── plugin.info
├── storage.js / .meta        — compression, localStorage, eviction, capture
├── startup.js / .meta        — hydrate from localStorage on load
├── save-hook.js / .meta      — th-saving-tiddler hook (auto-snapshot + state reset)
├── action-minver.js / .meta  — <$action-minver> widget (all operations)
├── preview-snapshots.tid     — editor preview pane (tagged $:/tags/EditPreview)
├── manager.tid               — standalone snapshot manager UI
├── settings.tid              — settings UI (tagged for core-hook hub)
├── styles.tid                — CSS (uses rr- theme classes where possible)
├── config-*.tid              — default configuration values
├── doc/                      — documentation (doc-template system)
│   ├── overview.tid
│   ├── architecture.tid
│   ├── reference.tid
│   ├── examples.tid
│   └── dev-workflow.tid
├── readme.tid, documentation.tid, changelog.tid
├── icon.tid, LICENSE.md, LICENSE.md.meta, README.md
```

!! Key implementation details

!!! Rollback rebuilds from scratch

Rollback does ''not'' merge snapshot fields with the draft (`new $tw.Tiddler(draft, snapshotFields)`). Instead, it builds a new tiddler containing only the snapshot's fields plus draft metadata (`title`, `draft.of`, `draft.title`). This ensures fields added after the snapshot are properly removed.

!!! Single-field rollback for missing fields

When rolling back a field that doesn't exist in the snapshot, the code rebuilds the draft without that field (copying all fields except the target). TW's `Tiddler` constructor ignores `undefined` values, so setting a field to `undefined` doesn't remove it.

!!! Compare state reset

The `th-saving-tiddler` hook deletes `$:/state/minver/compare/<title>` after saving, so the next edit session defaults back to "Compare Draft" instead of persisting a stale "Saved" selection.

!!! Compression pipeline

```
JSON.stringify(snapshots)
  → Blob → CompressionStream("deflate") → ArrayBuffer
  → btoa() → localStorage.setItem()
```

Decompression reverses the pipeline. Both are async (return Promises).

!! CSS conventions

* Plugin-specific classes use `mv-` prefix
* Reuses `rr-` theme classes: `rr-badge-rect`, `rr-muted`, `rr-small`, `rr-nowrap`, `rr-input`, `rr-input-row`, `rr-table`, `rr-link-btn`, `rr-callout`, `rr-badge-circle`, `rr-status-info`
* Icon buttons use shared `.mv-icon-btn` base with `.mv-icon-btn-danger` modifier for destructive actions

</$fill>
</$transclude>
