<$fill $name="body">

!! Action widget: `<$action-minver>`

|!Attribute |!Description |
|`op` |Operation: `snapshot`, `delete`, `delete-all`, `rollback`, `rollback-field`, `export`, `import`, `clean-all` |
|`title` |Original tiddler title (not the draft title) |
|`label` |Snapshot label (for `snapshot` op, optional — defaults to timestamp) |
|`draft` |Draft tiddler title (for `snapshot`, `rollback`, `rollback-field`) |
|`source` |`"draft"` or `"saved"` — which version to snapshot (default: `"draft"`) |
|`snapshot-id` |UUID of the target snapshot (for `delete`, `rollback`, `rollback-field`) |
|`field` |Field name (for `rollback-field` only) |

!! Operations

|!Op |!Description |
|`snapshot` |Capture current fields as a manual snapshot. Always saved to both wiki store and localStorage. |
|`delete` |Delete a single snapshot by ID. |
|`delete-all` |Delete all snapshots for a tiddler. |
|`rollback` |Replace all draft fields with snapshot fields. Fields not in the snapshot are removed. |
|`rollback-field` |Restore a single field from the snapshot. If the field doesn't exist in the snapshot, it is removed from the draft. |
|`export` |Serialize all snapshots from localStorage into `$:/minver/export` as JSON. |
|`import` |Load snapshots from `$:/minver/export` into localStorage and wiki store. |
|`clean-all` |Delete all snapshots from both localStorage and wiki store. |

!! Snapshot object format

```json
{
  "id": "uuid-v4",
  "timestamp": 1710000000000,
  "label": "snapshot-20260310..." | "my custom label",
  "type": "manual" | "auto",
  "fields": {
    "title": "My Tiddler",
    "text": "...",
    "tags": "tag1 tag2",
    "created": "20260310...",
    "modified": "20260310...",
    "custom-field": "value"
  }
}
```

All tiddler fields are captured as strings. Dates are stringified via `$tw.utils.stringifyDate()`, arrays via `$tw.utils.stringifyList()`. Draft-specific fields (`draft.of`, `draft.title`) are stripped — the original title is stored.

!! Temp tiddler layout

|!Tiddler |!Content |
|`$:/temp/minver/snapshots/<title>` |JSON array of snapshot objects for `<title>` |
|`$:/temp/minver/status` |`"loading"` or `"ready"` — hydration state |
|`$:/temp/minver/storage-usage` |Human-readable localStorage usage (e.g., "12.5 KB") |

!! Configuration tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Description |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/max-manual` |`3` |Max manual snapshots per tiddler |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/max-auto` |`3` |Max auto snapshots per tiddler |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/scope-filter` |`[all[]]` |Filter for which tiddlers get auto-snapshots |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/auto-to-storage` |`no` |Persist auto-snapshots to localStorage |

!! localStorage key format

Keys are prefixed with `minver:` followed by the tiddler title:

```
minver:My Tiddler → base64(deflate(JSON.stringify(snapshots)))
minver:$:/my-system-tiddler → base64(deflate(JSON.stringify(snapshots)))
```

!! Export/Import format

The export tiddler `$:/minver/export` contains a JSON object keyed by tiddler title:

```json
{
  "My Tiddler": [ { snapshot }, { snapshot }, ... ],
  "$:/system-tiddler": [ ... ]
}
```

Both auto and manual snapshots are included. Import merges with (overwrites) existing snapshots.

</$fill>
